<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Revolution 1, Wizards 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Joe-Max Moore scored his first goal of  
the season and Walter Zenga made seven saves as the New England 
Revolution shut out Kansas City 1-0 Saturday, extending the 
Wizards' record scoreless streak to 550 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wizards have been shut out in all three games this season  
and have not scored since Sept. 5. 
</P>
<P>
	Moore scored for the Revolution (1-1) in the 40th minute off a  
cross pass from defender Mike Burns. Johnny Torres had an assist on 
the play. 
</P>
<P>
	The Wizards (0-3) best scoring opportunity came in the 70th  
minute, when player-coach Zenga saved a diving header by Vincente 
Figueroa. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the first win for the Revolution at Arrowhead Stadium in  
five tries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
