<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clock Should Be Set Ahead One Hour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Daylight-saving time returns tonight.  
</P>
<P>
	The official moment of the change is at 2 a.m. local time  
Sunday, switching an hour of summer daylight from mornings to 
evenings. 
</P>
<P>
	Standard time returns Oct. 31 for most Americans.  
</P>
<P>
	A few places choose not to switch to daylight time, including  
Arizona, Hawaii, part of Indiana, Puerto Rico, the Virgin Islands 
and American Samoa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
