<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Behrens Wins Oaklawn Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOT SPRINGS, Ark. (AP) -- Favored Behrens overtook Littlbitlively  
early in the stretch run and easily won the $750,000 Oaklawn 
Handicap on today. 
</P>
<P>
	With regular rider Jorge Chavez aboard, the 5-year-old Behrens  
was not threatened in the stretch. He covered 1 1/8 miles on a sloppy 
track in 1:47 3-5 and won by 2 1/2 lengths. 
</P>
<P>
	Littlebitlively set all the pace and hung on for second. His  
stable mate, Precocity, the defending champion, passed some horses 
in the turn and ran third. 
</P>
<P>
	Littlebitlively and Dixie Road battled down the backstretch but  
Behrens and Archers Bay, 1-2 finishers in the Gulfstream Park 
Handicap on Feb. 27, were never far back. 
</P>
<P>
	Beherns paid $5, $2.80 and $2.60. The entry paid $2.80 and $3.  
</P>
<P>
	Heading into the far turn, Behrens and Archers Bay started  
moving on the leaders but Archers Bay couldn't keep up. 
</P>
<P>
	Behrens was coming off a 2 1/2-length victory in the Gulfstream  
Park Handicap, his first in a Grade I stakes and first victory 
since Sept. 20, 1997. 
</P>
<P>
	Littlebitlively was scratched from the Razorback Handicap  
because of an off track. Trainer Bobby Barnett said early in the 
week that Littlebitlively was doing as well as he was last November 
when he lost in a photo finish to Silver Charm. 
</P>
<P>
	Last year, Precocity prepared for the Oaklawn Handicap by  
finishing second in the New Orleans Handicap. A month ago, he won 
the New Orleans Handicap, beating Kentucky Derby and Preakness 
winner Real Quiet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
