<DOCNO> APW19990403.0035 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-03 14:12:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dodgers' Brown Buys Home in Georgia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Kevin Brown may call Georgia his home, but that  
doesn't mean he's going to live like a nomad while he's pitching 
for the Los Angeles Dodgers. 
</P>
<P>
	Brown, a former Georgia Tech star, and his wife, Candace, have  
bought the former Beverly Hills, Calif., home of musician John 
Fogerty for $3.8 million, The Atlanta Journal Constitution reported 
Saturday. The Browns also purchased the lot next door for $1.5 
million. 
</P>
<P>
	In the offseason, the Browns will live at the new home they're  
building on 60 acres in his hometown of Macon, 80 miles southeast 
of Atlanta. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dodgers raised the eyebrows -- and ire -- of several other  
teams in December by signing Brown to a record seven-year, $105 
million contract. 
</P>
</TEXT>
