<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Minor Quake Jostles Northern Calif. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLOVERDALE, Calif. (AP) -- A minor earthquake rattled Northern  
California late Saturday, but no injuries or damage were reported. 
</P>
<P>
	The quake, with a preliminary magnitude of 3.8, struck about 10  
p.m. near The Geysers power plants about 60 miles north of San 
Francisco, said Dale Cox, a spokesman for the U.S. Geological 
Service. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is a larger one for that particular area,'' he said, but  
``nothing unusual.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Six other smaller quakes, ranging from 1.5 to 2.9 in magnitude,  
also shook the area Saturday, Cox said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
