<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> DC United 1, MetroStars 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Roy Lassiter scored the only goal  
of the match two minutes into the second half to lift D.C. United 
to a 1-0 victory tonight against the New York-New Jersey 
MetroStars. 
</P>
<P>
	The game-winning goal came moments after Lassiter had just  
missed wide left following a cross from Jaime Moreno. 
</P>
<P>
	Moreno set the winning goal in motion when he passed to Marco  
Etcheverry just beyond the midfield stripe. Etcheverry then split 
the MetroStars' defense with a seeing-eye pass that put Lassiter in 
alone on goalkeeper Mike Ammann. 
</P>
<P>
	The United striker carried the ball inside the box before  
slipping a left-footed shot past Ammann into the right corner for 
his third goal of the season. 
</P>
<P>
	The MetroStars had two chances to score in the second half, but  
Eduardo Hurtado's shot in the 63rd minute hit off the left post and 
Hurtado's shot from the top of the box in the 73rd minute whistled 
wide right. 
</P>
<P>
	A red card to midfielder Billy Walsh in the 65th minute further  
diminished the MetroStars' chances. 
</P>
<P>
	The first half ended in a scoreless tie with neither team having  
a significant advantage. With a little more than eight minutes to 
play the MetroStars Mike Duhaney collided with United keeper Tom 
Presthus after Presthus had punched away a cross by Miles Joseph. 
</P>
<P>
	Both players fell to the ground with Presthus bleeding from the  
head and Duhaney from the nose. After a brief delay during which 
both players received medical attention, both continued in the 
match with Presthus receiving nine stitches at the half. 
</P>
</TEXT>
