<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Rochester Meats' Beef Recalled </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROCHESTER, Minn. (AP) -- Wholesale beef products produced at  
Rochester Meats were ordered recalled nationwide after federal 
inspectors found a dangerous strain of E. coli in samples collected 
last month. 
</P>
<P>
	The products recalled Wednesday include ground beef patties,  
ground chuck patties, chopped beefsteak, beef patties, meat for 
chili, beef patty mix and pure beef bulk. 
</P>
<P>
	The products were sold to wholesale and institutional customers  
in 10-, 15-and 20-pound packages. They were marked with the Julian 
code 8335 and Establishment 8999 in the inspection mark. 
</P>
<P>
	When ingested by humans, the E. coli bacterium can cause serious  
illness and sometimes death, especially in children and the 
elderly. 
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. Department of Agriculture has not confirmed any  
illnesses linked to the tainted meat, Joanne Randen, a Rochester 
Meats spokeswoman, said Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Karen Grzanek, vice president of quality assurance, said the  
recall is the company's first. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
