<HEADLINE> Time To Move Clock Ahead One Hour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- It's back.  
</P>
<P>
	That hour of evening sunshine for ball games and barbecues is  
back with the return of daylight-saving time. 
</P>
<P>
	The official moment for setting the clock ahead was 2 a.m.  
Sunday, though most folks did so before going to bed Saturday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
	Some, of course, forgot, and risked being late for church, work  
or other activities. 
</P>
<P>
	Standard time will return Oct. 31.  
</P>
<P>
	The exceptions -- where standard remains all year -- are Arizona,  
Hawaii, the part of Indiana in the Eastern time zone, Puerto Rico, 
the Virgin Islands and American Samoa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
