<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> La. Twister Kills 3, Injures 100 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BENTON, La. (AP) -- A tornado tore through this northwestern  
Louisiana town Saturday, flattening homes and trapping people 
inside when walls collapsed around them. 
</P>
<P>
	At least three were killed when the twister swept through a  
trailer park just north of Shreveport and destroyed at least 30 
house trailers. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're still searching and have so much to go through, there's  
no way of telling what the end total will be,'' said Bossier Parish 
Coroner Dawn Young. 
</P>
<P>
	KTAL-TV quoted sheriff's deputies and rescue workers on the  
scene saying there were six dead. Two died in a house trailer park 
and four others died in homes, KTAL reported. 
</P>
<P>
	About 100 people were injured, said Trooper Chris Johnson of the  
Louisiana State Police. Injuries ranged cuts and bruises to broken 
bones and more serious injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	The twister struck about 4 p.m. Some people were still missing  
Saturday night. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities went house to house looking for injured or dead, but  
decided they would have to bring in backhoes and front end loaders 
to remove fallen wall panels and roofs. They were also using dogs 
that are trained to find corpses and live accident victims. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's still a lot of rubble to sift through,'' Johnson said.  
</P>
<P>
	The center of destruction was the Hay Meadow Trailer Park.  
Twisted trees and flipped cars were mixed in with the wreckage of 
the house trailers, Johnson said. 
</P>
<P>
	``You can't even tell it was a trailer park,'' Johnson said.  
``It looks like a trash heap.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The National Weather Service said the twister was 300 yards wide  
when it passed through north Shreveport on its way to Benton. 
</P>
<P>
	KSLA-TV also reported that a tornado destroyed the First United  
Methodist Church in Logansport, a town southwest of Shreveport near 
the Texas border. 
</P>
<P>
	A tornado or severe winds also downed trees, damaged some homes  
and caused minor injuries in Shreveport, said Chuck Mazziotti, 
director of the Caddo Parish Office of Emergency Preparedness. 
</P>
<P>
	Benton resident Mary Maxwell said the tornado destroyed between  
15 and 20 homes in her neighborhood but didn't do any damage to her 
house. She said there were about seven trailers in the trailer 
park. 
</P>
<P>
	Residents had to use an ax to break through the wreckage of one  
trailer to extricate a family of five, she said. Another neighbor's 
large truck simply disappeared from the driveway. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's gone, they just can't find it,'' Maxwell said.  
</P>
<P>
	In Missouri, severe storms brought floodwaters across the  
southern part of the state. 
</P>
<P>
	Fifty people were evacuated to emergency shelters in the  
Bootheel as flash floods swept across Fredericktown. People were 
rescued from the roofs of homes, one of them carried to safety by a 
helicopter 
</P>
</TEXT>
