<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> At Least Nine Killed in La. Twister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BENTON, La. (AP) -- A tornado tore through this northwestern  
Louisiana town Saturday, flattening homes and trapping people 
inside when walls collapsed around them. At least nine people were 
killed. 
</P>
<P>
	The twister swept through trailer parks just north of  
Shreveport. 
</P>
<P>
	State police said six were killed at the Twin Point Trailer Park  
and three died at the Hay Meadow Trailer Park. At least 30 house 
trailers were destroyed in the Hay Meadow park. 
</P>
<P>
	About 100 people were injured, said Trooper Chris Johnson of the  
Louisiana State Police. Injuries ranged cuts and bruises to broken 
bones and more serious injuries. Local hospitals reported at least 
five people in critical conditon. 
</P>
<P>
	Hours after the afternoon twister hit, authorities were still  
looking for missing people, using police dogs and huge searchlights 
from nearby Barksdale Air Force Base. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's some children and moms missing in both trailer  
parks,'' said Lt. Mike Edmonson of the Louisiana State Police. 
</P>
<P>
	Bossier Parish Coroner Dawn Young said the death toll could rise  
even higher. 
</P>
<P>
	``We're still searching and have so much to go through, there's  
no way of telling what the end total will be,'' Young said. 
</P>
<P>
	In Missouri, Gov. Mel Carnahan declared a state of emergency in  
southern and east-central Missouri late Saturday night after severe 
storms caused flooding. 
</P>
<P>
	Louisiana authorities went house to house looking for injured or  
dead, but decided they would have to bring in backhoes and front 
end loaders to remove fallen wall panels and roofs. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnny Johnson, manager of the Silver Dollar Bingo, a cement  
block building next to the Hay Meadow trailer park, said about 20 
people were getting ready to start playing when the twister hit. 
</P>
<P>
	``All of a sudden it just sucked the doors open,'' he said.  
``The napkins, trash cans and everything else just all started 
moving around. The people just huddled together in the center of 
the room.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The tornado tore off part of the roof, but none of the players  
were hurt. 
</P>
<P>
	At the Hay Meadow Trailer Park, twisted trees and flipped cars  
were mixed in with the wreckage of the house trailers. 
</P>
<P>
	``You can't even tell it was a trailer park,'' Johnson said.  
``It looks like a trash heap.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The National Weather Service said the twister was 300 yards wide  
when it passed through north Shreveport on its way to Benton. 
</P>
<P>
	About the same time, a separate tornado destroyed the First  
United Methodist Church in Logansport, a DeSoto Parish town 
southwest of Shreveport near the Texas border. 
</P>
<P>
	And a tornado or severe winds also downed trees, damaged some  
homes and caused minor injuries in a Shreveport neighborhood. 
</P>
<P>
	In Missouri, severe storms brought floodwaters across the  
southern part of the state. 
</P>
<P>
	Fifty people were evacuated to emergency shelters in the  
Bootheel as flash floods swept across Fredericktown. People were 
rescued from the roofs of homes, one of them carried to safety by a 
helicopter 
</P>
<P>
	A 12-year-old boy was found dead in waist-deep water in a  
Fredericktown saw mill next to the flooded Caster River. The boy 
was moving equipment to higher ground to try and keep it dry. 
Authorities believe he died from an electrical shock. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
