<HEADLINE> Mom, Four Kids Die in Kentucky Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOUISVILLE, Ky. (AP) -- An early morning house fire killed a  
woman and four of her children Saturday and critically injured 
another child. 
</P>
<P>
	The bodies of the woman, Valeria Rutledge, 28, and her children  
were found in different locations in the house. 
</P>
<P>
	According to the Jefferson County Coroner's Office, Joshua  
Rutledge Taylor, 3; Brittany Rutledge Taylor, 4; and male and 
female twins Biantez and Bianca Rutledge Taylor, 7; also were 
pronounced dead at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
	Another girl, 13-year-old Clarisa Rutledge, was found outside  
the house and was listed in critical condition at University of 
Louisville Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire appeared to have started in the front of the house,  
where smoke detectors were installed, said acting Fire Chief Walter 
Lage. The cause remained under investigation. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire moved quickly through the house.  
</P>
<P>
	``When I came out my door, the whole house was on fire ... just  
flames everywhere,'' said neighbor Alfreda Morris. ``That was 
before anyone had even got there to try to put the fire out.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Relatives who live in the neighborhood said they had been with  
the victims only hours earlier. 
</P>
<P>
	``We were all together, just hanging out and laughing last  
night,'' said Nate Weaver, a cousin of the woman. ``There's nothing 
anyone can do now except pray. That's it.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
