<DOCNO> APW19990403.0110 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-03 12:12:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Blues Extend GM's Contract </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST.LOUIS (AP) -- The St. Louis Blues have added a year to the  
contracts of general manager Larry Pleau and assistant general 
manager John Ferguson. 
</P>
<P>
	Team president Mark Sauer said Saturday that both contracts had  
been extended through the 2001-2002 season. 
</P>
<P>
	Pleau and Ferguson both joined the Blues in 1997.  
</P>
<P>
	Blues coach Joel Quenneville is signed through the 2000-2001  
season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
